description:
&lt;p&gt;Enthusiastic and motivated Medicines Management Assistants are required to support the ward based clinical pharmacy services at Sheffield Teaching Hospitals Foundation Trust. The successful applicants will be able to demonstrate initiative and work to high standards of accuracy and reliability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Duties include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Label and dispense medication&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the Clinical Pharmacist and Medicines Management Technician with medication supply&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collect and deliver medicines to and from wards and departments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain appropriate drug stock levels at ward level or in theatres&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in the preparation of patients’ compliance aids&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage medication wastage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the transfer of patients’ medication between wards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will be based at the either the Northern General Hospital or the Hallamshire Hospital but you may be required to work in any of the sites across the trust when required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates will have some previous experience in a community or hospital pharmacy and will have completed a NVQ 2 qualification in Pharmacy Services (&lt;strong&gt;which must include the labelling and dispensing module&lt;/strong&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lisa Jones, 0114 2267050 Suzanne Hayes and Joanne Connolly on (0114) 2267051 or by email lisa.jones96@nhs.net, suzanne.hayes@nhs.net joanne.connolly7@nhs.net &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
